Preheat your oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @potatoes{600%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then into 1cm chips
(peeling optional).

Pop the chips onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with @Cajun Spice Mix{1%sachet}, @salt{to taste}
and @pepper{to taste} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.
Turn the tray halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

== Dressing and Salad ==

Boil a large #pot{} of salted water for the chicken.

Meanwhile, to make your dressing, add half the @Aioli{1%sachet} and
half the @Apple Cider Vinegar{1%sachet} to a #salad bowl{}. Mix well and
season to taste with salt and pepper.

Trim the @salad leaves{120%grams}. Reserve a leaf for each burger. Quarter the
remainder lengthways and separate the leaves.

Thinly slice the @tomato{1}.

== Pulled Chicken ==

Once the water is boiling, lower heat to medium-high then add the
@Irish Chicken Breast{320%grams} and a pinch of pepper. Cover and simmer
until the chicken is cooked, stirring halfway, ~{12-15%minutes}. Drain and set
aside.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging. Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal
> due to packaging we use to keep it fresh.

== Cheesy Chorizo Chips ==

Once the chips are cooked, carefully push them towards the centre of the
baking tray. Top with @chorizo{100%grams} and @grated cheese{50%grams} then
return to the oven until the cheese has melted, ~{6-8%minutes}.

== Assembly ==

Meanwhile, using two #forks{}, shred the chicken as finely as you can. Mix the
shredded chicken with @BBQ Sauce{2%sachets}, @Chipotle Paste{1%sachet},
remaining @Apple Cider Vinegar{1%sachet} and @sugar{1%tsp}. Mix to coat well
and season to taste with salt and pepper.

Meanwhile, pop the @Brioche Buns{2} into the oven to warm through,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Just before serving, toss the chopped salad leaves through the dressing.

To assemble the burgers, spread a spoonful of the remaining @Aioli{1%sachet}
over each base bun.

Top with reserved salad leaves, chipotle pulled chicken and sliced tomatoes.

Sandwich closed with the top bun.

Serve the salad, any remaining tomato slices and loaded chips alongside.